body:
In a workspace, when I define my feature-gated macro like this:

```rust
#[cfg(feature = "feat-a")]
macro_rules! foobar {
    ($type: ident) => {
        String
    };
}

#[cfg(not(feature = "feat-a"))]
macro_rules! foobar {
    ($type: ident) => {
        $type
    };
}
```

`cargo check` will not check all my packages. When I instead define them like this:

```rust
#[cfg(feature = "feat-a")]
mod mac {
    #[macro_export]
    macro_rules! foobar {
        ($type: ident) => {
            String
        };
    }
}

#[cfg(not(feature = "feat-a"))]
mod mac {
    #[macro_export]
    macro_rules! foobar {
        ($type: ident) => {
            $type
        };
    }
}
```

`cargo check` will check all my packages.

## Reproduction

Here's a replit with a minimum reproduction: https://replit.com/@TotempaaltJ/FaintImperfectPlot#pak-b/src/lib.rs

I'm linking directly to the relevant file. The setup is as follows: I have a workspace with (at least) three packages. They're defined as follows:

- **pak-a**  
  Depends on: pak-b  
  Feature: `feat-a = ["pak-b/feat-a"]`
- **pak-b**  
  Feature: `feat-a = []`
- **pak-c**  
  Depends on: pak-b
  No features

In `pak-b`, I use the feature as described above (first code block). Now if I run:

```sh
$ cargo check
    Finished dev [unoptimized + debuginfo] target(s) in 0.04s
```

Enabling the feature makes it work:

```sh
$ cargo check --features feat-a
    Checking pak-b v0.1.0 (/home/runner/Broken-feature-dependencies/pak-b)
    Checking pak-c v0.1.0 (/home/runner/Broken-feature-dependencies/pak-c)
    Checking pak-a v0.1.0 (/home/runner/Broken-feature-dependencies/pak-a)
    Finished dev [unoptimized + debuginfo] target(s) in 0.52s
```

Changing to the second codeblock makes it work as expected, without the feature enabled:

```sh
$ cargo check
    Checking pak-b v0.1.0 (/home/runner/Broken-feature-dependencies/pak-b)
    Checking pak-c v0.1.0 (/home/runner/Broken-feature-dependencies/pak-c)
    Checking pak-a v0.1.0 (/home/runner/Broken-feature-dependencies/pak-a)
    Finished dev [unoptimized + debuginfo] target(s) in 0.31s
```


### Meta
<!--
If you're using the stable version of the compiler, you should also check if the
bug also exists in the beta or nightly versions.
-->

`rustc --version --verbose`:
```
rustc 1.65.0
```

This also happens on nightly.
